I am the co-leader of a very small guild of average level = 42, and, as the most experienced folks in our guild are all casters, am looking for some advice on where we should be going re equipping our current main tank (human SK) and puller (woodelf ranger).  They are both fairly well equipped for level, I think, but am not one to judge such things, and we are wondering where we, with our limited resources (max field unit of two full groups, levels 35-51, support caster heavy, melees usually consisting of SK/Ranger/Rogue) should be looking toward in order to upgrade our melees, when the time comes.   <br>
<br>
Our SK is currently in Crustacean armor, using the Deathbringer's Rod we got her from KC (30/40 2HB) as her main weapon, and an FBSS our cleric scored in Guk <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Since she's a non-fattie, we are looking for a decend 1h (blunt or slashing) that she could use with a shield, when the occasion calls for it.  Our Ranger is currently in Ivy, using the Blackened Alloy bastard sword we got in Runnyeye EONS ago, but is still a very good and fast, although 2-handed, weapon.  We are trying to get her to start using two 1handed weapons, but she is married to that sword, it seems; some suggestions for something attainable by us that might light her fire would be appreciated.<br>
<br>
So, what should we be looking for, and where should we aim for, in terms of adventuring/questing for upgrades for them?  We're looking mainly for places we could go as a guild, as our folks (with a couple of exceptions) prefer killing/questing for their items, although Faervas and I do score some pickup raids from time to time, and our necro and SK will be joining us in the near future on those.<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for your advice,<br>
