<br>
once your sk hits 49, you can force him to pull his moss the old fashioned ugly way, the way we did it way back when when kunark first opened.<br>
<br>
Have the sk run up to the locked door.  have him use his word of shadow!!!!..<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ...then pull the resultant train to the base of the T, and feign when a reaver comes out to play....he can &quot;warrior feign&quot; too, if need be.  Have your ranger harmony the resultant train.  Have the ranger pull the black reaver.  Kill the reaver over and over untill it spawns a lord. Note that every time you kill a reaver it has a chance of spawning either another reaver or the lord.  4 of the possible 7 reavers spawn shades...if rak ashir spawns....DO NOT ATTACK RAK'ASHIR (sorry, old guild joke).  Just try again for another lord.  Kill the lord.  The moss is the COMMON drop from the lord that pops from the very first reaver.  <br>
<br>
The reavers can only be hit by lures, as far as magic goes, so hit him with all the rest of your tanks and any pets.  The rest of the casters deal with any adds.  We pulled the reavers to the north (left?) side of the zone, as that is the side that to which you can get out of the water.  Reavers are nice practice for a low level guild for the &quot;main tank&quot; strategy, of having your main tank build up aggro and then be the only one who needs healing....it helps if your main tank is on a lan and can peek on the computer next to him to watch his character position for when the reaver procs a blind.<br>
<br>
Alternatively...buy my moss for the low low price of 2k...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But it's much more fun to do it on your own.<br>
<br>
As for yer ranger...married to 2 handers? i've got this silver swiftblade i've been aching to dump....<br>
<br>
As for plate armor...well, i've been selling Valus Custodus Plate for the past few weeks at about 250pp per peice.  It'll do until your guild hits fear and hate, as it has similar ac to fear/hate armor, but without the resists. (but with lots of STR instead!)<br>
<br>
Last thing...got a ranger? it's time for you guys to hit trakanon's teeth and pull the forager/hunter cycle.  You should be able to handle just about anything but &quot;Doom&quot; for which you can probably ask assistance.<br>
<br>
